messages.title: CAMBRIDGE CANDIDATE VOTED WITH NICK CLEGG'S LIB DEM GOVERNMENT 782 TIMES WHEN HE WAS CAMBRIDGE MP
messages.content: The leaflet criticizes the former MP for voting with the previous government on key issues.

messages.title: Our NHS is in crisis
messages.content: The leaflet highlights the current state of the NHS and implies a need for better measures and improvements.

keyPolicies.policyDescription: The leaflet suggests the NHS is in crisis and needs better support and measures.
The leaflet advocates for keeping the local area green and preventing overdevelopment.
The leaflet suggests that the Labour party has radical and fair proposals, presumably in contrast to the current government's policies, though specifics are not provided.

issues.health: The leaflet highlights the crisis in the NHS suggesting a need for improvements.

housing.content: The leaflet suggests measures to keep the Chesterton area green, which might imply a stance on housing development.

leaflet.additionalNotes: The leaflet contains a number of 'FAILED' stamps across different boxes, which suggest criticisms of the former MP's actions while in government partnership with Nick Clegg's Lib Dems.
